name: AwsVolumeTemplate
description:
Configuration template for AWS EBS volumes.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.gkemulticloud.v1.AwsVolumeTemplate

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.size_gib
params.description: Optional. The size of the volume, in GiBs. When unspecified, a default value is provided. See the specific reference in the parent resource.

params.name: data.volume_type
params.description: Optional. Type of the EBS volume. When unspecified, it defaults to GP2 volume.

params.name: data.iops
params.description: Optional. The number of I/O operations per second (IOPS) to provision for GP3 volume.

params.name: data.kms_key_arn
params.description: Optional. The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Customer Managed Key (CMK) used to encrypt AWS EBS volumes. If not specified, the default Amazon managed key associated to the AWS region where this cluster runs will be used.
